<sec id="sec9-1077546312445595"><title>5. Results and decisions</title>
<p>From the obtained curves presented in <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig2-1077546312445595">Figure 2</xref>, it can be noted that the relative movement modulus (Z) is increasing and decreasing in respect to frequency ratio ω/ω<sub>n</sub>.</p>
<p>It can be noted that if the relative frequency value approaches the accelerometer natural frequency, the resonant frequency (ω = ω<sub>n</sub>) will appear. The accelerometer can operate properly and at the same time avoid the resonance, however the relative frequency must be equal or less than (ω<sub>n</sub>/3). The accelerometer is chosen in relation to the vibration frequency gain.</p>
<p>Two tests are carried out in order to choose a better value of damping rate to limit a measurement error to a minimum value. The obtained results are illustrated by the curves presented in <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig6-1077546312445595">Figure 6</xref> of the accelerometer damping rate. By comparing these two figures, it can be concluded that the best value of damping rate to limit the measurement error to 1% is 0.675.</p>
<p>In <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig7-1077546312445595">Figure 7</xref>, the measurement error versus relative movement modulus with different values of damping rate is presented.</p>
</sec>
<sec id="sec10-1077546312445595"><title>6. Conclusion</title>
<p>In this work an accelerometer mathematical model is developed and proposed to choose the best damping rate value to limit the measurement error to 1%.</p>
<p>From this model the equations of relative movement modulus and measurement error of the accelerometer in relation to damping rate and frequency ratio are determined.</p>
<p>The obtained results from computer simulation have shown that a suitable damping rate can minimize measurement error of relative movement to a minimum value. Using the presented model, the damping rate and precision error of the accelerometer can be improved.</p>
<p>In future work, it is important to study the accelerometer reliability to determine vibration level with great accuracy.</p>
</sec>
